@emph{Written by Thomas Hieber, @email{thieber@@gmx.net}.  Last updated 19
March 2000.}

Currently, Crystal Space has reached a state where it can be very rewarding to
create some maps for Crystal Space.  That's where @file{map2cs} comes in
handy.  It allows you to convert maps created with mature Quake map building
tools to Crystal Space's map format.

People new to @file{map2cs} may be interested in the accompanying tutorial
(@pxref{map2cs Tutorial}), and all users (new and old) may benefit from the
accompanying reference information which follows.

